{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3714", "repo": "rails", "body": "Thanks but I don't think we should add this feature to serialization. If your serialization is becoming too complex, it is a major sign that you need to use another tool and not the to_xml or to_json methods. The complexity of options we already accept today lead to something I like to call HDD (Hash Driven Development) and it is something we should be avoiding and not making more complex.", "_id": {"$oid": "523832bebd3543c15100f900"}, "issue_id": 3714, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2832394", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3714#issuecomment-2832394", "updated_at": "2011-11-22T09:51:23Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim", "login": "josevalim", "gravatar_id": "e837f6b7fd146ab16ed3d663476c063e", "html_url": "https://github.com/josevalim", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/e837f6b7fd146ab16ed3d663476c063e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fe20b21ae6508f22fc189c60a0880d0b8.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 9582, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/josevalim/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-11-22T09:51:23Z", "id": 2832394, "owner": "rails"}
